        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-05T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="901" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d901">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/3–2945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-05T20:00:00-04:00">April 5, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1366. Bonnet has informed Department that his Government is much concerned over
                    delay in receiving invitation to join Reparations Commission.</p>
                <p>French already know of our approval (see Department’s 1229, March 29<note n="40" xml:id="d901fn40">See footnote 17, <ref target="#pg_1179">p.
                        1179</ref>.</note>). Since Soviet, British and American governments are all
                    agreed on desirability of French participation and since Commission is to
                    function in Moscow, Ambassador Harriman has been instructed to inform Soviet
                    authorities that we expect them to extend the invitation to the French in behalf
                    of the participating governments.</p>
                <p>Please inform Bidault.<note n="41" xml:id="d901fn41">Georges Bidault, Minister
                        for Foreign Affairs, Provisional Government of the French Republic.</note>
                    London is being asked to inform Eden.<note n="42" xml:id="d901fn42">Anthony
                        Eden, British Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
